   "source": [
    "<div style=\"background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a3a5c 0%, #2d6a9f 100%); padding: 30px 40px; border-radius: 12px; color: white; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n",
    "  <h1 style=\"color: white; font-size: 2em; margin: 0 0 8px 0;\">Physics-Informed Geo-AI for Irrigation Quantification</h1>\n",
    "  <p style=\"color: #c8dff0; font-size: 1.05em; margin: 0;\">\n",
    "    A hybrid framework integrating AlphaEarth satellite embeddings with the Inverse-SM2RAIN hydrological model\n",
    "  </p>\n",
    "  <hr style=\"border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3); margin: 16px 0;\">\n",
    "  <p style=\"color: #c8dff0; margin: 0; font-size: 0.95em;\">\n",
    "    <strong style=\"color:white;\">Platform:</strong> I-GUIDE Spatial AI Challenge &nbsp;|&nbsp;\n",
    "    <strong style=\"color:white;\">Region:</strong> California Central Valley &nbsp;|&nbsp;\n",
    "    <strong style=\"color:white;\">Author:</strong> Esmaeel Adrah, Daniel Dominguez\n",
    "  </p>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "Irrigation is the largest agricultural water use, yet total withdrawal volumes and their contributions to groundwater recharge remain poorly quantified. Data driven remote sensing methods often miss deep percolation losses and require hardly availble ground truth data, while hydrological models remain restricted in their ability to incorporating wide range of environmental variables. To overcome this, the project integrates satellite embeddings, spatial AI models, and grid-based geospatial hydrological frameworks. Initial results show strong performance in estimating irrigation volumes. The framework enables large-scale irrigation monitoring, enhancing understanding of human-environment interactions and supporting evidence-based water sustainability planning across socio-economic and environmental contexts.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook presents a novel **Physics-Informed Geo-AI** framework designed to estimate agricultural irrigation quantity. We integrate the high-dimensional predictive power of **TabNet** with the mechanistic rigor of the **Inverse-SM2RAIN** hydrological model, utilizing Earth Observation data to fill critical gaps in water management data.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Core Innovation: Parameterizing the Physical Environment\n",
    "\n",
    "The primary innovation of this work is the **hybridization of satellite foundation model embeddings with mechanistic soil–water balance equations**. Unlike typical Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN) approaches that focus solely on numerical curve-fitting, this framework **parameterizes the physical environment** using satellite-derived data. Rather than predicting irrigation as a direct \"black-box\" output, the model learns latent environmental properties encoded in **AlphaEarth embeddings** and maps them to the specific physical parameters ($Z$, $K$, $b$) required by the SM2RAIN formulation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Scientific Hypothesis\n",
    "\n",
    "We hypothesize that **AlphaEarth satellite embeddings** capture latent geophysical signatures — such as soil texture, porosity, and hydraulic conductivity — which are the primary drivers of surface soil moisture dynamics. By mapping these embeddings to the parameters of the **SM2RAIN soil-water balance equation**, we ensure that irrigation estimates are not merely statistical correlations but are **physically constrained** by the fundamental laws of hydrology.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Technical Framework\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | Component | Description |\n",
    "|------|-----------|-------------|\n",
    "| 1 | **Feature Extraction** | AlphaEarth Foundation Model embeddings as high-level land surface representations |\n",
    "| 2 | **Neural Parameterization** | TabNet maps embeddings to SM2RAIN physical parameters ($Z$, $K$, $b$) |\n",
    "| 3 | **Physical Constraint Layer** | Inverse-SM2RAIN equation derives volumetric irrigation from learned parameters |\n",
    "| 4 | **Responsible AI** | Multi-objective loss with physical penalties (non-negativity, ET caps, regional bounds) |"
   ]
  },
