   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. Physics-Informed Model Architecture & Illustrative Training\n",
    "\n",
    "This section defines the core **Physics-Informed Geo-AI** architecture, integrating TabNet's tabular learning capability with the mechanistic rigor of the Inverse-SM2RAIN hydrological model.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Model Design\n",
    "\n",
    "**Physics-Informed Parameter Prediction**  \n",
    "The neural network estimates three physical parameters required by the SM2RAIN equation:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Parameter | Symbol | Physical Meaning | Range |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Root-zone soil water capacity | $Z$ | Depth of active soil layer | 10–2,000 mm |\n",
    "| Hydraulic conductivity coefficient | $K$ | Saturated drainage rate | 0.001–5.0 mm/day |\n",
    "| Nonlinear drainage exponent | $b$ | Pore structure nonlinearity | 1–11 |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Residual Error Term ($E$)**  \n",
    "A dedicated output head predicts a bounded residual correction ($E \\in [-1.5, 1.5]$) to account for sub-grid heterogeneity, measurement noise, and structural limitations of the physical model.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Multi-Objective Physics-Constrained Loss**  \n",
    "Training minimizes a composite loss designed to enforce physically plausible predictions:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Negative Penalty** — forces irrigation estimates to remain non-negative\n",
    "- **ET Penalty** — prevents irrigation from exceeding 1.2× actual evapotranspiration\n",
    "- **Cap Penalty** — constrains outputs to ≤ 10 mm/day (Central Valley regional limit)\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #e6a817; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 4px; margin-top: 16px;\">\n",
    "<strong>⚙️ Computational Note:</strong> To comply with I-GUIDE platform constraints, the notebook runs an <strong>illustrative 30-epoch training loop on CPU</strong> (~1–2 minutes). For full scientific inference, the pre-trained model weights are loaded in Section 4. Final results are based on the pre-trained weights, not this illustrative loop.\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
