    "---\n",
    "## 5. Physics-Informed Inference & Irrigation Volumetric Estimation\n",
    "\n",
    "With pre-trained weights loaded, this section performs a **forward pass** across the full dataset to estimate irrigation volumes and compare them against USGS reference data. This stage represents the transition from *latent satellite embeddings* → *physical parameters* → *volumetric water estimates*.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Implementation Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | Operation | Detail |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **Forward Pass** | TabNet inference | Maps AlphaEarth embeddings to $Z$, $K$, $b$ parameters |\n",
    "| **Physical Equation** | Inverse-SM2RAIN | $I = (Z \\cdot \\Delta SM) - P_r + (K \\cdot SM^b) + ET$ |\n",
    "| **Post-processing** | Physical guardrails | Non-negativity clip, precipitation masking ($P_r > 0 \\Rightarrow I = 0$), 10 mm/day cap |\n",
    "| **Validation** | Distribution & time series | Histogram of irrigation magnitudes + single-pixel seasonal check |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Physical Constraint:** Irrigation is set to zero on days when precipitation exceeds 0 mm, as supplemental irrigation is physically redundant during rainfall events."
   ]
  },
