    "---\n",
    "## 6. Regional Validation: USGS Benchmarking at HUC-12 Scale\n",
    "\n",
    "This section evaluates model accuracy by aggregating pixel-level predictions to the **Hydrologic Unit Code 12 (HUC-12)** scale and comparing them against **USGS reference data** — a standard benchmark for regional water district reporting.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Validation Methodology\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | Detail |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Spatial Aggregation** | 1 km pixel predictions → HUC-12 watershed boundaries |\n",
    "| **Unit Conversion** | Depth (mm) → Volume (Million Gallons per Day, MGD), accounting for HUC-12 acreage |\n",
    "| **Hydro-Climatic Context** | Irrigation time series overlaid with precipitation hyetograph to verify hydrologic logic |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Performance Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "| Metric | Purpose |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Pearson $r^2$** | Captures the model's ability to reproduce seasonal trends and timing |\n",
    "| **Nash-Sutcliffe Efficiency (NSE)** | Rigorous hydrological benchmark evaluating absolute volumetric accuracy |"
   ]
  },
